snippet: The killing of Brandon Lincoln Woodard was captured on surveillance video, but law enforcement officials said no arrest was imminent.
abstract: Killing of Brandon Lincoln Woodard in Midtown Manhattan in December 2012 was captured on surveillance video, but law enforcement officials say no arrest is imminent; veteran former detectives say it is not unusual for a complex case to take many months to unravel, eventually turning on the bravado of those involved or their ties to other crimes.
lead_paragraph: The killing of Brandon Lincoln Woodard was captured on surveillance video, but law enforcement officials said no arrest was imminent.

headline.seo: Answers Elusive 6 Months After Killing of Brandon Woodard in Manhattan
headline.main: Answers Elusive 6 Months After a Fatal Shooting in Manhattan
headline.print_headline: Answers Remain Elusive 6 Months After a Fatal Shooting on a Manhattan Street
